ompt_tokens": 655, "total_tokens": 655}, "id": "46b2c4d3-5579-96cc-994f-9a4ccf1bb6ec"}, "input": {"input": ["躯体疾病:躯体疾病是指身体上的疾病，包括感染、代谢紊乱等，这些疾病不仅可能引发明显的身体症状，如疼痛、瘙痒、鼻塞和呼吸困难，还可能导致精神障碍，其严重程度与精神症状的轻重密切相关。躯体疾病的诊断需要仔细排除严重的器质性疾病，因为其症状可能与躯体形式障碍相似，但本质上是由于身体上的病理变化引起的。此外，躯体疾病如疼痛、瘙痒、鼻塞和呼吸困难等，还可能引起入睡困难和睡眠不深，进一步影响患者的整体健康和生活质量。", "躯体疾病及精神活性物质所致精神障碍:Mental disorders caused by physical illnesses or psychoactive substances, which can lead to acute or chronic mental health issues", "躯体疾病所致精神障碍:\"躯体疾病所致精神障碍\" (Mental Disorders Due to Physical Diseases) refers to a category of mental health conditions that arise as a direct consequence of physical illnesses. These disorders can manifest in both acute and chronic forms, often emerging during the most severe phases of the underlying physical disease. The condition is characterized by a range of psychiatric symptoms that are secondary to the primary physical illness. Management of these mental disorders typically occurs within general hospital settings, where both the physical and mental health aspects of the patient can be addressed concurrently. This condition underscores the intricate connection between physical health and mental well-being, highlighting the importance of a holistic approach to treatment.", "转换性感觉障碍:转换性感觉障碍主要表现为转换性感觉麻木和感觉丧失。症状表现不符合感觉神经的分布。其中，视觉障碍很少是完全性的，多为视野模糊或“管状视野”。\"", "转换性症状:转换性症状是一种由精神障碍引起的身体症状，通常与抑郁症或精神分裂症相关", "转换性癔症:A psychological disorder affecting voluntary motor or sensory functions, with symptoms suggesting neurological or general physical conditions. It is accompanied by psychological factors, and symptoms are not consciously produced or feigned. Diagnosis involves ruling out physical conditions and ensuring symptoms cause significant distress or functional impairment.", "转换性精神障碍:A psychological condition characterized by the conversion of mental stress into physical symptoms", "转换性运动障碍:转换性运动障碍多表现为一个或几个肢体的全部或部分丧失功能；瘫痪可为部分性的，即运动减弱或运动缓慢，也可为完全性的；可有各种形式和程度的共济失调，尤以双腿多见；也可有一个或多个肢端或全身的夸张震颤。\"", "轻度认知障碍:轻度认知障碍（MCI）是血管性痴呆的早期症状之一，主要表现为近记忆损害，不能集中注意力，专注于某一项工作的能力下降等", "轻抑郁:A milder form of depression with less severe symptoms>"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}